      "content": "i see. so if i'm writing this from the perspective of a historian, it sounds like they really leaned into these metrics to create a hierarchy. can you expand on how they used those specific metrics—like the cranial measurements or the IQ findings—to explain why one race was considered \"superior\" or \"more advanced\" than others? like, what was the actual logic they used to link those physical traits to societal success or civilization? I want to make sure I get the specific reasoning right for the paper.",
